I was reading a forum analysis on Neon Genesis Evangelion and how lots of episodes had a late afternoon scene where the sunset bathes a room the pilots are in with orange light and it hints at how everything will later melt into LCL at the end of the Human Instrumentality Project

But it strikes me as something that does occur in reality. Early evening, the sunset, those deep orange hues seem to enforce the unity of existence. Everyone's story of the day comes together at that hour. You tend to better perceive the relations between everyone in those times.

Once sunlight deepens into the orange or red spectrums you intuitively start to feel how your day was related to the other person's day and influenced by it. Separate stories turn into one with the nightfall. Loose ends coming together. A microcosm of the day of Final Judgement.
